'''Kumobe Kurumazuka Kofun''' (雲部車塚古墳) is an ancient Kofun ({{ill|Kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|12=draft}}) located in {{ill|Tamba Sasayama|ja|丹波篠山市|12=draft}}, Hyogo Prefecture. The mound is keyhole-shaped ({{ill|Zenpokoenfun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|12=draft}}).

The identity of the interred individual remains unknown, but the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|12=draft}} has Historic Site1 the tumulus as the "Kumobe {{ill|Mausoleum Reference Site|ja|陵墓参考地|1=Mausoleum Reference Site|12=draft}}," associating it with {{ill|Tanba-no-Michinushi no Mikoto|ja|丹波道主命|12=draft}}, a grandson of the 9th Emperor {{ill|Kaihō Tennō|ja|開化天皇|12=draft}}. 

With its size Ranked first in the Tamba region and second in Hyogo Prefecture, the kofun dates to the mid-5th century (mid-{{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|12=draft}}). 

== Overview ==

[[File:751121 Kmb Kurumaduka Kofun aerial.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Aerial view of Kumobe Kurumazuka Kofun}}]]

Situated in eastern {{ill|Tamba Sasayama|ja|丹波篠山市|12=draft}} along the Tamba basin's edge where it connects with the {{ill|Kameoka basin|ja|亀岡盆地|12=draft}}, this keyhole-shaped kofun stands as a strategic and significant site in the region. 
