'''Kumobe Kurumazuka Kofun''' (雲部車塚古墳) is an ancient Kofun ({{ill|Kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|qq=draft}}) located in {{ill|Tamba Sasayama|ja|丹波篠山市|qq=draft}}, Hyogo Prefecture. The mound is keyhole-shaped ({{ill|Zenpokoenfun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft}}).

The identity of the interred individual remains unknown, but the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|qq=draft}} has Historic Site1 the tumulus as the "Kumobe {{ill|Mausoleum Reference Site|ja|陵墓参考地|1=Mausoleum Reference Site|qq=draft}}," associating it with {{ill|Tanba-no-Michinushi no Mikoto|ja|丹波道主命|qq=draft}}, a grandson of the 9th Emperor {{ill|Kaihō Tennō|ja|開化天皇|qq=draft}}. 

With its size Ranked first in the Tamba region and second in Hyogo Prefecture, the kofun dates to the mid-5th century (mid-{{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft}}). 

