'''Kumobe Kurumazuka Kofun''' (雲部車塚古墳) is an ancient Kofun ({{ill|Kofun|ja|古墳|1=Kofun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun|qq=}}) located in {{ill|Tamba Sasayama|ja|丹波篠山市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamba Sasayama|qq=}}, Hyōgo Prefecture. The mound is keyhole-shaped ({{ill|Zenpokoenfun|ja|前方後円墳|1=Zenpokoenfun|1=Zenpokoenfun|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Zenpokoenfun|13=User:Immanuelle/Zenpokoenfun|qq=}}).

The identity of the interred individual remains unknown, but the {{ill|Imperial Household Agency|ja|宮内庁|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Imperial Household Agency|qq=}} has Historic Site1 the tumulus as the "Kumobe {{ill|Mausoleum Reference Site|ja|陵墓参考地|1=Mausoleum Reference Site|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Mausoleum Reference Site|13=User:Immanuelle/Mausoleum Reference Site|qq=}}," associating it with {{ill|Tanba-no-Michinushi no Mikoto|ja|丹波道主命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanba-no-Michinushi no Mikoto|qq=}}, a grandson of the 9th Emperor {{ill|Kaihō Tennō|ja|開化天皇|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kaihō Tennō|qq=}}. 

With its size Ranked first in the Tamba region and second in Hyōgo Prefecture, the kofun dates to the mid-5th century (mid-{{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kofun period|qq=}}). 

== Overview ==

[[File:751121 Kmb Kurumaduka Kofun aerial.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Aerial view of Kumobe Kurumazuka Kofun}}]]

Situated in eastern {{ill|Tamba Sasayama|ja|丹波篠山市|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tamba Sasayama|qq=}} along the Tamba basin's edge where it connects with the {{ill|Kameoka basin|ja|亀岡盆地|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kameoka basin|qq=}}, this keyhole-shaped kofun stands as a strategic and significant site in the region. 
...



