'''Kumobe Kurumazuka Kofun''' (雲部車塚古墳) is an ancient Kofun ([[:en:Kofun|Kofun]]) located in [[:en:Tamba-Sasayama|Tamba Sasayama]], Hyōgo Prefecture. The mound is keyhole-shaped ([[:en:Zenpokoenfun|Zenpokoenfun]]).

The identity of the interred individual remains unknown, but the [[:en:Imperial Household Agency|Imperial Household Agency]] has Historic Site1 the tumulus as the "Kumobe {{ill|Candidate Imperial Mausoleum|ja|陵墓参考地|1=Candidate Imperial Mausoleum|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Candidate Imperial Mausoleum|13=User:Immanuelle/Candidate Imperial Mausoleum|qq=}}," associating it with {{ill|Tanba-no-Michinushi no Mikoto|ja|丹波道主命|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tanba-no-Michinushi no Mikoto|qq=}}, a grandson of the 9th Emperor [[:en:Emperor Kaika|Kaihō Tennō]]. 

With its size Ranked first in the Tamba region and second in Hyōgo Prefecture, the kofun dates to the mid-5th century (mid-[[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]]). 

== Overview ==

[[File:751121 Kmb Kurumaduka Kofun aerial.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Aerial view of Kumobe Kurumazuka Kofun}}]]

Situated in eastern [[:en:Tamba-Sasayama|Tamba Sasayama]] along the Tamba basin's edge where it connects with the {{ill|Kameoka basin|ja|亀岡盆地|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kameoka basin|qq=}}, this keyhole-shaped kofun stands as a strategic and significant site in the region. 
...



