With its size Ranked first in the Tamba region and second in Hyōgo Prefecture, the kofun dates to the mid-5th century (mid-[[:en:Kofun period|Kofun period]]). 

== Overview ==

[[File:751121 Kmb Kurumaduka Kofun aerial.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Aerial view of Kumobe Kurumazuka Kofun}}]]

Situated in eastern [[:en:Tamba-Sasayama|Tamba Sasayama]] along the Tamba basin's edge where it connects with the {{ill|Kameoka basin|ja|亀岡盆地|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kameoka basin|qq=|1=Kameoka Basin|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11181997}}, this keyhole-shaped kofun stands as a strategic and significant site in the region. 
...



